### Probation Tracker MCP — debug HTTP tests
### Use with the VS Code "REST Client" (humao.rest-client) extension.
### Press the "Send Request" link above each request.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@tunnelMcp     = https://f0r8gwwh-3001.uks1.devtunnels.ms/mcp
@localMcp      = http://localhost:3001/mcp
@tenantId      = 0c2614e6-a76a-433c-80fd-88ac91e67b9d
@calendarMcp   = https://agent365.svc.cloud.microsoft/agents/tenants/0c2614e6-a76a-433c-80fd-88ac91e67b9d/servers/mcp_CalendarTools

# App registration (both probation and calendar plugins use SSO via TDP).
@clientId      = 54881055-411d-41b2-8f25-f1312a1abfe6

# Bearer token for /mcp and /calendar-mcp. Obtain via:
#   az login --tenant 0c2614e6-a76a-433c-80fd-88ac91e67b9d
#   az account get-access-token --resource api://auth-82726735-4a55-4f56-a5c5-3f35ade6cb9c --query accessToken -o tsv
# (Paste the eyJ... value below.)
@bearer        = eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6IndoMDZzRWt6TEhKNXNOTmFVeVJZMl82TzhLMCJ9..kZWirOZ_DTlVxgJhZZkjK0flmaUuXRGqVUoyZvLhByISH3GOkT3taNkzJPqQHcZx-8wxDAlUGGfCntKHRyh7pf8UjhSUU3PdEjZrTS0lk4xMPauFMB_9-B73gH1oS4l0ahh9PWQUtMqHorXdX5O0F4Uz1MkzFxjsmYLp3r8EZeUBNwVLB2CqHp8UyJbCIdU2EXYoJMsCrtLJ98WWF1ZO72-6Lt2jVQFGk25eU48-hqnHc4WP-zuF9xPRiFNyo5S9x2n5Joj_JVFFhO_x1lFWb8B-Jn4KhLf-tAIXZRgOnl9_fxGlk-FtwE2MzuDzl3uN1MahWNkeMSBbC5tV5V0PZA

# Common headers (MCP Streamable HTTP)
@accept        = application/json, text/event-stream
@mcpVersion    = 2025-06-18
# Anchor mailbox = your UPN; many Substrate-fronted services require this.
@anchorMailbox = phi-lay@TestTestTOLTest.onmicrosoft.com

# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 1 — Local probation MCP server (no auth)
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 1.1 Health probe (root)
GET http://localhost:3001/

### 1.2 initialize (REQUIRED first call per MCP spec)
# @name probLocalInit
POST {{localMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{bearer}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 1,
  "method": "initialize",
  "params": {
    "protocolVersion": "2025-06-18",
    "capabilities": {},
    "clientInfo": { "name": "rest-client", "version": "0.0.1" }
  }
}

### 1.3 tools/list
POST {{localMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{bearer}}

{ "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 2, "method": "tools/list" }

### 1.4 resources/list (should return 3 ui://probation/*.html resources)
POST {{localMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{bearer}}

{ "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 3, "method": "resources/list" }

### 1.5 tools/call → show-probation-dashboard (no filters)
POST {{localMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{bearer}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 4, "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "show-probation-dashboard",
    "arguments": {}
  }
}

### 1.6 tools/call → show-probationer-detail by name
POST {{localMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{bearer}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 5, "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "show-probationer-detail",
    "arguments": { "name": "Sarah" }
  }
}

### 1.7 tools/call → show-probation-reports
POST {{localMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{bearer}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 6, "method": "tools/call",
  "params": { "name": "show-probation-reports", "arguments": {} }
}

### 1.8 Read a UI resource
POST {{localMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{bearer}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 7, "method": "resources/read",
  "params": { "uri": "ui://probation/dashboard.html" }
}

